'''Thiago Ezequiel Almada''' (born 26 April 2001) is an Argentine professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] or [[winger (association football)|winger]] for {{Spanish football updater|Atlético Madrid}} club [[Atlético Madrid]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]].

Almada was a member of the Argentina team that won the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], making history by becoming the first active [[Major League Soccer]] player to win the tournament. He also won the [[2024 Copa Libertadores]] and the [[2024 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|Brazilian Série A]] with [[Botafogo FR|Botafogo]].

== Early life ==
Thiago 'Guayo' Ezequiel Almada was born on 26 April 2001, in [[Ciudadela, Buenos Aires]] in [[Argentina]].<ref name=atlutd.ta/> He grew up in the neighborhood [[Fuerte Apache|Ejército de los Andes]], also referred to as Fuerte Apache, which is known for high crime rates and prevalent drug use.<ref>{{Cite web |last=SeventhQueen |date=28 August 2019 |title=LN – The evil called Fuerte Apache, a neighborhood marked by stigmas |url=https://basi-spanish.com/ln-the-evil-called-fuerte-apache-a-neighbourhood-marked-by-stigmas/ |access-date=23 September 2021 |website=About Argentina |language=es-AR}}{{Dead link|date=July 2024 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Almada spent many of his early years selling fruit and vegetables door-to-door to earn extra money. Much time was spent with his grandparents while his parents worked.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Thiago Almada: Argentina's next great playmaker on Man City's radar |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/thiago-almada-argentina-playmaker-man-city/1si536etb6tmx1fnyui4xivyom |access-date=23 September 2021 |website=Goal.com |archive-date=10 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310173424/https://www.goal.com/en/news/thiago-almada-argentina-playmaker-man-city/1si536etb6tmx1fnyui4xivyom |url-status=live}}</ref>

== Club career ==

=== Vélez Sarsfield ===
At the age of four, Almada played football for a local club, Santa Clara. He was picked up by Vélez Sarsfield at age five, where he made his way through the youth academy. On 10 August 2018, just four months after his 17th birthday, Almada made his professional debut against [[Newell's Old Boys]] in a 2-0 victory and scored his first two goals on 5 November in the 3-2 loss against [[Defensa y Justicia]], both in the [[2018–19 Argentine Primera División|2018 Argentine Primera División]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=5 November 2018 |title=Doblete de Thiago Almada: La joyita de Vélez empezó a dar sus frutos - TyC Sports |url=https://www.tycsports.com/nota/superliga/2018/11/05/doblete-de-thiago-almada-la-joyita-de-velez-empezo-a-dar-sus-frutos.html |access-date=5 September 2025 |website=www.tycsports.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.clarin.com/deportes/futbol/thiago-almada-centennial-fuerte-apache-ilusiona-velez_0_BJpvTo2B7.html |title=Thiago Almada, el centennial de Fuerte Apache que ilusiona a Vélez |date=2 October 2018 |access-date=18 December 2022 |archive-date=17 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221117232954/https://www.clarin.com/deportes/futbol/thiago-almada-centennial-fuerte-apache-ilusiona-velez_0_BJpvTo2B7.html |url-status=live}}</ref> In October 2018, he was included in [[The Guardian]]'s "Next Generation 2018".<ref>{{cite web |date=11 October 2018 |title=Next Generation 2018: 60 of the best young talents in world football |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2018/oct/11/next-generation-2018-60-of-the-best-young-talents-in-world-football |work=The Guardian |accessdate=12 October 2018 |archive-date=10 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190810004249/https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2018/oct/11/next-generation-2018-60-of-the-best-young-talents-in-world-football |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Atlanta United ===

==== Signing and 2022 season ====
On 4 December 2021, Vélez Sarsfield announced that it had reached an agreement with [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Atlanta United FC|Atlanta United]] for the pre-transfer of Almada in February 2022.<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 December 2021 |title=La noche del 10 |trans-title=The night of the 10 |url=https://velez.com.ar/futbol/notas/2021/12/04/020350_la-noche-del-10 |access-date=6 December 2021 |publisher=[[Club Atlético Vélez Sarsfield]] |language=es |archive-date=25 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220925235758/https://velez.com.ar/futbol/notas/2021/12/04/020350_la-noche-del-10 |url-status=live}}</ref> The transfer, reportedly worth a league-record $16 million, was officially announced by Atlanta on 9 February 2022.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Atlanta United acquires Thiago Almada from CA Vélez Sarsfield &#124; Atlanta United FC |url=https://www.atlutd.com/news/atlanta-united-acquires-thiago-almada-from-ca-velez-sarsfield-argentina |access-date=9 February 2022 |archive-date=9 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220209153908/https://www.atlutd.com/news/atlanta-united-acquires-thiago-almada-from-ca-velez-sarsfield-argentina |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last= |first= |title=Thiago Almada to move to Atlanta United for MLS-record $16 million fee, Argentine club says |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4184594/2021/12/03/thiago-almada-to-move-to-atlanta-united-for-mls-record-16-million-fee-argentine-club-says/ |access-date=9 February 2022 |work=The New York Times |language=en |archive-date=26 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220926001300/https://theathletic.com/news/thiago-almada-to-move-to-atlanta-united-for-mls-record-16-million-fee-argentine-club-says/AQD2XO3jL8bx/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Almada was unveiled in the club's kit the next day in a welcome ceremony that was held virtually due to the ongoing [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 February 2022 |title=Atlanta United acquires Thiago Almada from CA Velez Sarsfield |url=https://www.atlutd.com/news/atlanta-united-acquires-thiago-almada-from-ca-velez-sarsfield-argentina |access-date=15 February 2022 |publisher=[[Atlanta United FC]] |language=en |archive-date=9 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220209153908/https://www.atlutd.com/news/atlanta-united-acquires-thiago-almada-from-ca-velez-sarsfield-argentina |url-status=live}}</ref> His signing was met with scrutiny by Atlanta fans due to the use of a racially insensitive gesture with his eyes during a recent goal celebration; Almada apologized shortly after being asked about the situation.<ref>{{Cite web |date=11 February 2022 |title=Atlanta United newcomer Thiago Almada apologizes to Atlanta United supporters |url=https://www.ajc.com/sports/atlanta-united/almada-apologizes-to-atlanta-united-supporters/ |access-date=15 February 2022 |publisher=[[Atlanta Journal-Constitution]] |language=en}}{{Dead link|date=July 2024 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

On 14 February, Almada made his official debut for Atlanta wearing the number 8 against [[C.D. Guadalajara]] during the team's pre-season tour of Mexico. Atlanta would end up losing the match 3–0.<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 February 2022 |title=Thiago Almada debuts in Atlanta United's 3–0 defeat to Guadalajara, Dom Dwyer starts in 3–0 loss against Tepatitlan FC |url=https://www.dirtysouthsoccer.com/2022/2/13/22931878/atlanta-united-loses-3-0-to-c-d-guadalajara-in-preseason-friendly/ |access-date=15 February 2022 |publisher=[[Dirty South Soccer]] |language=en |archive-date=15 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220215140613/https://www.dirtysouthsoccer.com/2022/2/13/22931878/atlanta-united-loses-3-0-to-c-d-guadalajara-in-preseason-friendly/ |url-status=live}}</ref> He made his MLS debut against expansion team [[Charlotte FC]] on 15 March as a substitute in Atlanta's 2–1 win.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.atlutd.com/news/cronica-del-partido-atlanta-united-gano-contra-charlotte-fc-thiago-almada-debut|language=es|title=Crónica del Partido: Atlanta United demostró su jerarquía contra Charlotte FC con marcador final de 2-1|website=atlutd.com|access-date=23 April 2026|first=Samantha|last=Garcia|date=13 March 2022}}</ref> Almada scored his first goal for the club in a 3–3 draw with [[CF Montréal]] four days later. The goal would end up winning the MLS Goal of the Week contest for Matchday 4.<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 March 2022 |title=Thiago Almada's screamer wins MLS AT&T Goal of The Week for Matchday 4 |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/thiago-almada-s-smasher-wins-mls-week-4-at-t-goal-of-the-week |access-date=22 April 2022 |publisher=[[Major League Soccer]] |language=en |archive-date=26 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220426013841/https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/thiago-almada-s-smasher-wins-mls-week-4-at-t-goal-of-the-week |url-status=live}}</ref>

On November, he was awarded 2022 MLS Newcomer of the Year after being chosen in the MLS Team of the Week five times, including back-to-back on 12 and 15 September, becoming the second Atlanta United player ever to earn that prize.<ref>{{Cite web |last=atlutd |title=Thiago Almada Named 2022 MLS Newcomer of the Year {{!}} Atlanta United FC |url=https://www.atlutd.com/news/thiago-almada-named-2022-mls-year-end-newcomer-of-the-year-award-miguel-almiron |access-date=5 September 2025 |website=atlutd |language=en}}</ref>

==== 2023 season ====
On 25 February 2023, Almada scored two goals (one of which was a [[Free kick (association football)|free kick]]) in the first game of the [[2023 Major League Soccer season|2023 season]], helping Atlanta gain a 2–1 win over [[San Jose Earthquakes]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Booth |first=Chuck |date=26 February 2023 |title=Free kick excellence from Thiago Almada sees Atlanta United to an opening day victory |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/free-kick-excellence-from-thiago-almada-sees-atlanta-united-to-an-opening-day-victory/ |access-date=26 February 2023 |website=CBS Sports |language=en-US |archive-date=26 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226101938/https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/free-kick-excellence-from-thiago-almada-sees-atlanta-united-to-an-opening-day-victory/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Schirru |first=Francesco |date=26 February 2023 |title=Almada superstar: dal Mondiale vinto alla doppietta d'oro nel primo match post Qatar |url=https://www.goal.com/it/notizie/almada-argentina-mls-dove-gioca-atlanta/bltaabceacddd632aac |access-date=26 February 2023 |website=Goal.com |language=it-IT |archive-date=26 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226103546/https://www.goal.com/it/notizie/almada-argentina-mls-dove-gioca-atlanta/bltaabceacddd632aac |url-status=live}}</ref> As a result, Almada was named MLS Player of the Week,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Robertson |first=Doug |date=28 February 2023 |title=Atlanta United's Thiago Almada voted MLS player of the week |url=https://www.ajc.com/sports/atlanta-united/atlanta-uniteds-thiago-almada-voted-mls-player-of-the-week/X2PPSTPY35F6HHYXHCN57MDSRY/ |access-date=28 February 2023 |work=[[The Atlanta Journal-Constitution]] |archive-date=28 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230228222540/https://www.ajc.com/sports/atlanta-united/atlanta-uniteds-thiago-almada-voted-mls-player-of-the-week/X2PPSTPY35F6HHYXHCN57MDSRY/ |url-status=live}}</ref> as well as being featured in the league's Team of the Matchday.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sigal |first=Jonathan |date=28 February 2023 |title=Team of the Matchday: Who shined brightest on MLS is Back weekend? |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/team-of-the-matchday-who-shined-brightest-on-mls-is-back-weekend |access-date=28 February 2023 |work=[[Major League Soccer]] |archive-date=9 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230309154011/https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/team-of-the-matchday-who-shined-brightest-on-mls-is-back-weekend |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Botafogo ===
On 6 July 2024, Almada officially joined [[Botafogo FR|Botafogo]], of [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]], signing a five-year contract with the club. The deal reportedly commanded a fee of [[$]]21 million ([[€]]19,5 million) plus $9 million (€7,5 million) in add-ons, in the process, it broke the transfer record both for the MLS, and the Brazilian football.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Redação |date=6 July 2024 |title=Botafogo anuncia contratação de Thiago Almada, campeão do mundo pela Argentina |url=https://fogonarede.com.br/botafogo-anuncia-contratacao-de-thiago-almada-campeao-do-mundo-pela-argentina/ |access-date=9 July 2024 |website=Fogo na Rede |language=pt-br}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Botafogo in a 2-1 win against [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista|Corinthians]] for the [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/esportes/brasileirao/botafogo-vence-o-corinthians-com-brilho-de-almada-e-abre-vantagem-na-lideranca/|title=Botafogo Vence o Corinthians com brilho de Almada e abre vantagem na liderança|date=19 September 2024|publisher=CNN Brasil|language=pt}}</ref> In this short stint at Botafogo, Almada conquered the [[2024 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] and [[2024 Copa Libertadores]], being one of the main players on the team and becoming one of the fans’ favorites, guaranteeing his place in the eternal pantheon of the club’s greatest players.<ref>{{Cite web |last=BARROSO FURTADO |first=ENRICO |title=O IMPACTO DA ECONOMIA NO FUTEBOL ARGENTINO EM COMPARAÇÃO AO FUTEBOL BRASILEIRO |publisher=Faculdades Catolicas |url=https://doi.org/10.17771/pucrio.acad.70828}}</ref>

==== Loan to Lyon ====
On 19 December 2024, Almada announced that he would join [[Ligue 1]] side [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] on 5 January 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Foot : Thiago Almada annonce son arrivée à l'OL le 5 janvier |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Thiago-almada-annonce-son-arrivee-a-l-ol-le-5-janvier/1527460 |access-date=19 December 2024 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> Lyon announced his arrival on 15 January 2025, as loan deal until 30 June 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ol.fr/fr/actualites/l-olympique-lyonnais-annonce-l-arrivee-de-thiago-almada|title=L'Olympique Lyonnais annonce l'arrivée de Thiago Almada|date=15 January 2025|publisher=Olympique Lyonnais|language=fr}}</ref>

===Atlético Madrid===
On 15 July 2025, [[La Liga]] club [[Atlético Madrid]] announced that they had reached an agreement with Botafogo for the transfer of Almada.<ref>{{cite web |date=15 July 2025 |title=Acuerdo con el Botafogo para el traspaso de Thiago Almada |trans-title=Agreement with Botafogo for the transfer of Thiago Almada |url=https://www.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/acuerdo-con-el-botafogo-para-el-traspaso-de-thiago-almada |accessdate=16 July 2025 |publisher=[[Atlético Madrid]] |language=es}}</ref>

==International career==
Almada played for the [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina under-20]] squad in 2019, before featuring for the [[Argentina national under-23 football team|under-23]] squad in 2021.

His debut in the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]] came on 23 September 2022, in Miami, during a friendly match against [[Honduras national football team|Honduras]].

In November 2022, Almada was officially called up to the Argentina [[2022 FIFA World Cup|World Cup]] squad to replace injured [[Joaquín Correa]], only five days before Argentina's first game of the tournament.<ref>{{cite tweet |number=1593352407299153920 |user=Argentina |title=El futbolista Thiago Almada se suma a la convocatoria mundialista de Qatar 2022. |author=Argentina national football team |author-link=Argentina national football team |date=17 November 2022 |access-date=17 November 2022 |language=es |trans-title=Thiago Almada has been added to the squad for Qatar 2022.}}</ref> He was a member of the squad that ultimately won the tournament, becoming the first active MLS player to win a World Cup.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Vertelney |first1=Seth |title=Thiago Almada becomes first active MLS player to win World Cup |url=https://prosoccerwire.usatoday.com/2022/12/18/almada-become-first-active-mls-player-to-win-world-cup/ |website=[[USA Today]] |publisher=[[Gannett]] |access-date=23 January 2023 |date=18 December 2022}}</ref> In Argentina's final group stage game, he made his 2022 World Cup debut against [[Poland national football team|Poland]]. He came on in the 83rd minute as a substitute of [[Alexis Mac Allister]] in which Argentina was victorious by 2–0.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2 December 2022 |title=Thiago Almada reacts to historic World Cup debut with Argentina |url=https://www.90min.com/posts/thiago-almada-reacts-historic-world-cup-debut-argentina |access-date=24 March 2023 |website=90min.com |language=en-GB |archive-date=24 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230324151921/https://www.90min.com/posts/thiago-almada-reacts-historic-world-cup-debut-argentina |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 23 March 2023, Almada scored his first international goal for Argentina at the senior level during a friendly against [[Panama national football team|Panama]] in his third appearance for the senior team, becoming the first-ever MLS-based player to score for the national team.<ref>{{cite web |last=Sigal |first=Jonathan |title=Thiago Almada scores for Argentina as Lionel Messi hits 800 career goals |website=mlssoccer |date=24 March 2023 |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/thiago-almada-scores-for-argentina-as-lionel-messi-hits-800-career-goals |access-date=23 April 2024 |archive-date=30 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231130114252/https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/thiago-almada-scores-for-argentina-as-lionel-messi-hits-800-career-goals |url-status=live}}</ref>

Almada competed for [[Argentina at the 2024 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web |title=ALMADA Thiago |url=https://olympics.com/en/paris-2024/athlete/thiago-almada_1929998 |work=[[Paris 2024 Olympics]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241006142210/https://olympics.com/en/paris-2024/athlete/thiago-almada_1929998 |archive-date=6 October 2024}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Almada was reported for a case of alleged sexual abuse after a party in [[San Isidro, Buenos Aires]] that occurred on 4 December 2020. A 28-year-old woman stated that she was sexually abused whilst unconscious by Almada, along with Vélez central defender [[Miguel Brizuela]] and the former [[Argentino de Quilmes]] coach [[Juan José Acuña Delbene]] in a house rented by [[Juan Martín Lucero]].

According to the victim's account, which was corroborated by a witness, she went up to one of the rooms in order to have consensual sex with Almada, but drank something that began to make her ill. Then, Brizuela and another woman entered the room and started to do various unconsented sexual acts to her. The victim stated that she had never wanted to include Brizuela, and that the three people continued even though she was screaming that she did not want anything to do with it.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Grabia |first=Por Gustavo |date=9 February 2021 |title=Imputaron a los jugadores de Vélez Thiago Almada y Miguel Brizuela en la causa por abuso sexual |url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes/2021/02/09/la-fiscal-imputo-a-los-jugadores-de-velez-thiago-almada-y-miguel-brizuela-en-la-causa-por-abuso-sexual/ |access-date=5 September 2025 |website=infobae |language=es-ES}}</ref>

After the investigation became public, his club suspended both him and Miguel Brizuela.<ref>{{Cite web |date=9 February 2021 |title=Argentina's Velez suspends players charged with sexual abuse |url=https://apnews.com/article/buenos-aires-argentina-soccer-thiago-sexual-abuse-9dacbd266ed17eb82208f22ab885feeb |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210923175628/https://apnews.com/article/buenos-aires-argentina-soccer-thiago-sexual-abuse-9dacbd266ed17eb82208f22ab885feeb |archive-date=23 September 2021 |access-date=23 September 2021 |website=AP NEWS |language=en}}</ref> A week after Almada was suspended, he was reinstated with the club stating, "substantial modifications were generated by virtue of the incorporation of new evidence, expertise and testimonies."<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 February 2021 |title=Vélez Sarsfield reinstated Thiago Almada and Miguel Brizuela to the squad |url=https://lapelotita.com/2021/02/16/velez-sarsfield-reinstated-thiago-almada-and-miguel-brizuela-to-the-squad/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211116115213/https://lapelotita.com/2021/02/16/velez-sarsfield-reinstated-thiago-almada-and-miguel-brizuela-to-the-squad/ |archive-date=16 November 2021 |access-date=23 September 2021 |website=La Pelotita (Wayback Machine) |language=en-US}}</ref>

In February 2021, Almada and Brizuela were charged with sexual abuse with the aggravating circumstances of carnal access and group abuse by prosecutor Laura Zyseskind. Acuña Delbene became a fleeing felon after being charged in December 2020, but was arrested at his home in [[Quilmes]] in July 2021,<ref>{{Cite web |date=30 July 2021 |title=Detuvieron al técnico de fútbol acusado de abusar sexualmente de una mujer en un asado junto a jugadores de Vélez |url=https://www.infobae.com/sociedad/policiales/2021/07/30/detuvieron-al-tecnico-de-futbol-acusado-de-abusar-sexualemente-de-una-mujer-en-un-asado-junto-a-jugadores-de-velez/ |access-date=5 September 2025 |website=infobae |language=es-ES}}</ref> while Almada and Brizuela are still awaiting sentencing by the Argentine court.

Despite the charges, Almada was called up by [[Lionel Scaloni]] to play for the Argentine national team in the 2022 FIFA World Cup. This decision sparked controversy in Argentina and led to widespread international criticism of [[Argentine Football Association|AFA]]'s decisions. The victim's attorney pointed out several irregularities in the case because, according to FIFA and AFA regulations, "a player is not allowed to be part of a national team if the team can certify that he has a pending criminal case."<ref>{{Cite web |date=7 December 2022 |title=Thiago Almada y una investigación por abuso sexual - Feminacida |url=https://www.feminacida.com.ar/thiago-almada/ |access-date=5 September 2025 |language=es}}</ref>

